351
00:18:59.476 --> 00:19:03.376
informal care arrangements where we can provide a koha so we're not draining

352
00:19:03.416 --> 00:19:07.136
family, but we're not necessarily entering into that formal employment

353
00:19:07.236 --> 00:19:11.106
contract." And it means having that trust base with the

354
00:19:11.256 --> 00:19:14.536
person that you're having those conversations with, your NASC or your EGL,

355
00:19:15.136 --> 00:19:18.936
and being able to work out what's going to work best for the whole

356
00:19:19.036 --> 00:19:19.676
family.

357
00:19:20.036 --> 00:19:20.396
Mm.

358
00:19:20.476 --> 00:19:23.916
And yes, family provides care. I think we all agree that that

359
00:19:23.976 --> 00:19:24.476
