404
00:21:47.876 --> 00:21:51.136
My name's Ross Porter. I'm a board member of FASD CAN Incorporated.

405
00:21:51.176 --> 00:21:55.076
It's a national charitable organization representing people living

406
00:21:55.136 --> 00:21:56.856
with fetal alcohol spectrum disorder

407
00:21:57.836 --> 00:22:00.376
and families and whanau who support them.

408
00:22:00.536 --> 00:22:04.076
FASD is a lifelong disability. People living with it

409
00:22:04.096 --> 00:22:07.566
typically have profound challenges with memory, decision-making,

410
00:22:07.756 --> 00:22:08.656
impulse control,

411
00:22:09.596 --> 00:22:11.036
and understanding consequences.

412
00:22:11.276 --> 00:22:15.116
Many need support every day, not just as children, but throughout their

413
00:22:15.156 --> 00:22:17.796
adult lives. There is no cure for FASD.

414
00:22:19.016 --> 00:22:22.676
Right now, only around one in five people we represent qualify for

415
00:22:22.696 --> 00:22:26.136
disability support services because of how eligibility is currently

416
00:22:26.156 --> 00:22:29.796
defined. The other 80% are left without funded

417
00:22:29.876 --> 00:22:32.316
support, relying almost entirely on their families.

418
00:22:32.956 --> 00:22:36.896
That's already an injustice, and this bill, as drafted, risks

419
00:22:37.016 --> 00:22:38.896
making it permanent and worse.

420
00:22:39.976 --> 00:22:43.916
Our most serious concern is Clause 11, the power given to the minister alone

421
00:22:43.936 --> 00:22:47.316
to determine who is eligible for disability support.

422
00:22:48.456 --> 00:22:51.756
To explain why this matter, I just want to tell you about a typical family

423
00:22:51.796 --> 00:22:52.496
situation.

424
00:22:54.276 --> 00:22:57.856
Their adult son, I'll call him James, has FASD along with an

425
00:22:57.876 --> 00:23:01.796
intellectual disability. His IQ has been assessed at 68, so

426
00:23:01.836 --> 00:23:05.056
he does qualify for disability support services.

427
00:23:05.436 --> 00:23:08.626
Qualifying on paper and actually receiving reliable support

428
00:23:09.476 --> 00:23:11.876
has turned out to be two very different things.

429
00:23:12.376 --> 00:23:13.456
James is 26,

430
00:23:14.456 --> 00:23:16.756
can't manage money, can't hold down a job.

431
00:23:20.856 --> 00:23:22.676
He cannot live safely alone.

432
00:23:23.676 --> 00:23:26.136
His mother has been his carer since he was born.

433
00:23:26.616 --> 00:23:29.756
She's now in her late 50s. She has her own health problems,

434
00:23:31.676 --> 00:23:35.076
and she has almost no savings because she gave up her career to take up

435
00:23:35.156 --> 00:23:37.376
part-time work, which allows her to care for him.

436
00:23:38.576 --> 00:23:42.536
Even with James meeting the eligibility criteria, his mother has spent years

437
00:23:42.576 --> 00:23:46.056
fighting the system just to get the level of support he's entitled to.

438
00:23:46.736 --> 00:23:49.276
His funding has been reassessed and reduced twice.

439
00:23:50.896 --> 00:23:54.636
This is what happens to a family today under a system that already involves a

440
00:23:54.696 --> 00:23:56.716
measure of administrative discretion.

441
00:23:57.856 --> 00:24:01.636
Clause seven, allowing the minister to redefine who qualifies

442
00:24:02.096 --> 00:24:04.116
and on what terms without

443
00:24:05.456 --> 00:24:09.436
parliamentary scrutiny and democracy, not requiring consultation with

444
00:24:09.456 --> 00:24:12.724
the Disability Community Panel- It could be changed in time.

445
00:24:13.244 --> 00:24:16.614
It's creating a lot of uncertainty for those families,

446
00:24:17.524 --> 00:24:20.584
and probably fear of what might happen.

447
00:24:22.004 --> 00:24:25.564
Clause eight, the family first principle, means that whenever

448
00:24:25.804 --> 00:24:29.684
support is reduced or delayed, James' mother will be

449
00:24:29.704 --> 00:24:33.684
expected to fill the gap with no assessment of what that costs

450
00:24:33.804 --> 00:24:36.064
her in terms of her health or

451
00:24:37.244 --> 00:24:39.624
her financial position. We're not asking

452
00:24:40.884 --> 00:24:41.144
the

453
00:24:42.484 --> 00:24:46.264
committee to oppose the bill. We accept that a legislative framework is

454
00:24:46.284 --> 00:24:49.284
needed following the Fleming judgment.

455
00:24:49.484 --> 00:24:51.604
What we are asking is that parliament,

456
00:24:52.624 --> 00:24:56.564
not a minister acting alone, retains meaningful control over who

457
00:24:56.604 --> 00:24:58.184
receives disability support.

458
00:24:59.544 --> 00:25:02.944
I've got some recommendations here, but hopefully you've got my submission in front

